  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How does counselling for andhra pradesh students work?",
  "response": "Counselling for students in Andhra Pradesh, particularly for higher education admissions (like engineering, medicine, etc.), follows a structured process. Here\u2019s a general overview of how it typically works:\n\n1. **Announcement of Results and Ranks:**\n   After the entrance examinations (like EAMCET for engineering and agriculture, NEET for medical courses), results and ranks are announced.\n\n2. **Notification for Counselling:**\n   The respective authorities (like APSCHE for EAMCET) will issue a notification detailing the counselling schedule, process, and necessary documentation.\n\n3. **Registration:**\n   Students need to register online for counselling. This involves filling in personal details, educational qualifications, and paying the counselling fee.\n\n4. **Verification of Documents:**\n   Students must attend the designated helpline centres to get their documents verified. The required documents typically include:\n   - Entrance exam rank card and hall ticket.\n   - 10th and 12th grade mark sheets.\n   - Transfer certificate.\n   - Caste certificate (if applicable).\n   - Income certificate (if applying for fees reimbursement).\n   - Local status certificate.\n\n5. **Option Entry:**\n   After document verification, students can choose their preferred colleges and courses online. They need to list down their choices in order of preference.\n\n6. **Seat Allotment:**\n   Based on the rank, reservation, and choices filled by the students, the seat allocation process takes place. Students can check their allotment online.\n\n7. **Reporting to College:**\n   Once a seat is allotted, the student must download the allotment order and report to the allotted college within the given timeline to complete the admission process, including paying the college fees.\n\n8. **Second Round of Counselling:**\n   If seats remain vacant, a second round of counselling may be conducted. Students who didn\u2019t get a seat or want to change their allotted seat can participate again.\n\n9. **Special Counselling:**\n   Occasionally, special rounds of counselling may be conducted for seats that remain vacant even after the second round. This could accommodate students who didn\u2019t participate earlier or didn\u2019t get a seat.\n\nThroughout this process, it is crucial for students to stay updated with official notifications and guidelines from the conducting authority\u2019s website.",
